Author:
Vol / Page:   3/807
Edition:
Quote:  (Queen Charlotte Sound) We observ'd already that the principal fish caught by the seyne were Mullets [ed. fn Aldrichetta forsteri.] and Elephant fish [ed. fn  Callarhyncus milli.] & a few soles [ed. fn  Peltorhamphus novaeseelandiae.] and flounders, [ed.fn Rhombosalea spp.] but those which the Indians mostly supply'd us with are a sort of sea Bream of a silver colour with a black spot on the neck, [ed. fn Tarakihi, ...] ...
